About this hotel

On 3 hectares of gardens and olive groves, this elegant hotel is 7 km from the Majorelle Garden and 12 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport.

    The Werki.s3 months ago on Google
    2/5
    (Translated by Google) The best part was the chicken tagine
    Unfortunately, the hotel is getting on in years and the situation with Corona seems to have affected the hotel quite a bit. We stayed 5 days for a friend's 
    (Translated by Google) The best part was the chicken tagine
    Unfortunately, the hotel is getting on in years and the situation with Corona seems to have affected the hotel quite a bit. We stayed 5 days for a friend's wedding at the Murano Resort (close to the wedding location) and unfortunately it turned out to be completely different than expected. The rooms are unfortunately quite outdated and really not nice. The pools are okay, but again lack the necessary eye for detail.
    The outdoor facilities seem to be restored, at least some gardeners and craftsmen were on the way.
    Unfortunately, the breakfast was really below average and, like the rooms, should definitely be improved.

    Annakhil

    The sprawling suburb of Annakhil includes golf courses and palm groves, with paths and horse-carriage tours through 100,000 trees at El Palmeral. Inside that park is Muse de la Palmeraie, showing a century of Moroccan paintings in a 1940s colonial farmhouse. MACAAL is a more modern space, displaying pan-African art. Residential areas have casual tagine restaurants, while resort hotels have chic bars and bistros.

    About this hotel

    On 3 hectares of gardens and olive groves, this elegant hotel is 7 km from the Majorelle Garden and 12 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport.

    Unfussy rooms feature free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs, and tea and coffeemaking equipment. Warmly furnished upgraded rooms add balconies. Suites have sitting areas and terraces.

    There are 4 outdoor pools, as well as a spa area, a snug restaurant, and indoor and poolside bars.
